quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  21,25,"And We did not send any Noble Messenger before you, but We divinely revealed to him that, “There is no God except I (Allah), therefore worship Me alone.”"
  21,26,"And they said, “The Most Gracious has chosen a son – Purity is to Him! In fact they are honourable bondmen.”"
  21,27,"They do not speak before He has, and they act only at His command."
  21,28,"He knows what is before them and what is behind them, and they do not intercede except for him whom He likes, and they fear with awe of Him. (The Holy Prophets and virtuous people will be given the permission to intercede. Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him – will be the first to intercede.)"
  21,29,"And the one among them who says, “I am a God beside Allah” – We shall reward him with hell; this is how We punish the unjust."
  21,30,"Did not the disbelievers observe that the heavens and the earth were together, so We parted them, and we made every living thing from water? So will they not accept faith?"
  21,31,"And We have placed mountains as anchors in the earth so that it may not shake with them; and We kept wide roads in it, so that they may find guidance."
  21,32,"And We have made the sky a roof, protected; and they turn away from its signs."
  21,33,"And it is He Who created the night and the day, and the sun and the moon; each one floats in an orbit."
  21,34,"And before you, We did not appoint on earth a never-ending life for any human; will they, if you depart, become immortal?"
  21,35,"Every living being must taste death; and We test you with harm and with good – a trial; and to Us only you have to return."
